sub_title: Double Degree Student at Erasmus University Rotterdam
summary:
Studying at Erasmus University Rotterdam, I have obtained critical assets to bridge the gap between society, environment, and economy to promote sustainable and inclusive development. Additionally, I have developed a philanthropic and pragmatic approach to development through involvement in the student association Positive Impact Society Erasmus (PISE), which provides training and practices that align with Effective Altruism.

Apart from my studies, I follow an internship program at Nuffic Southern Africa. My goal is to effectively allocate European Union budget in the agenda of Southern African countries and promote mutual goals through the application of theory of change. In doing so, I expect to gain a holistic perspective into global development programs and enhance their effectiveness in local contexts.

As an international student constantly exposed to change and dynamism, I find motivation in learning from diverse surroundings and disciplines. Therefore I am interested in topics such as Anthropology, Organisational Psychology, Data Analytics, Computer Science, Biology, and Healthcare.
